        <div class="shortNote">
            <h3>TYPES OF DONATION</h3>
            <p>
                The average human body contains about five liters of blood, which is made of several cellular and
                non-cellular components such as <b>Red blood cell, Platelet</b>, and <b>Plasma.</b></p>

            <p>Each type of component has its unique properties and can be used for different indications. The donated
                blood is separated into these components by the blood centre and one donated unit can save upto four
                lives depending on the number of components separated from your blood.</p>
            <div class="two-col-note">
                <div style="padding: 5px 15px;text-align: center; margin-right: 2px solid gray;">
                    <h4 style="margin-bottom: 10px;">How long does it take to donate?</h4>
                    <p>
                        <b>15-30 minutes</b> to donate.including the pre-donation check-up.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="hr" style="padding: 5px 15px; text-align: center;">
                    <h4 style="margin-bottom: 10px;">How often can I donate?</h4>
                    <p><b>Male</b> donors can donate again after <b><i>90 days</i></b> and <b>female</b> donors can
                        donate
                        again after
                        <b><i>120 days.</i></b>
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
